                            "title": "Eye of Horus ",
                            "description": "<p>Horus was a good son, offering his left eye in exchange for restoring his father, Osiris, to eternal rule over the underworld. The “eye of Horus,” called <i>udjat</i>, is now a familiar symbol of protection and sacrifice and is painted on Tashat’s wrappings, or <i>cartonnage</i>. Like Horus, Tashat must offer Osiris her physical body in exchange for her spiritual life.</p>\n",
