                            "title": "Inside the Coffin",
                            "description": "<p>Incredible images and inscriptions once decorated the inside of Tashat’s coffin, ancient artwork now hidden by a thick black substance. No, it’s (probably) not cursed. During mummification, Tashat’s body and wrappings may have been painted with a clear liquid, like resin, to prevent water damage. The resin was likely mixed with pitch (a sticky brown substance) for extra protection. Over time, the pitch seeped through the wrappings into the wooden coffin.</p>",
