                            "description": "<p>There is no single reason for Shiva’s four arms, but multiple arms typically suggest a god’s immense power, and the ability to perform many tasks at once. Typically, four arms indicate a god in a beneficent attitude, while multiple arms portray an active, warlike mode. In one hand, Shiva holds a <em>damaru </em>drum, emitting what some experts interpret as the rhythmic sound of creation. In another, he makes the <em>abhaya mudra</em>, a gesture of protection from evil.</p>"
