                            "title": "Evolution of a Painting",
                            "description": "<p>Beckmann’s journals reveal his evolving views about the painting and its subject. He changed the title six times between 1944 and 1945, from <em>The Concert</em> to the <em>Great Café</em>, from the<em> Great Bar</em> to the <em>Great Cabaret</em>, and finally from the <em>Ox-Feast</em> to <em>Blind Man’s Buff</em>.</p>"
