                            "title": "What's He Thinking?",
                            "description": "<p>Ganymede has a pretty good poker face. You can’t tell if he’s enjoying his eagle experience or concerned. Thorvaldsen, like many artists of his time, felt that timeless art was grounded in universal human characteristics, like reason and intellect, more than individual differences like emotion. So he focuses on Ganymede’s interior experience rather than any exterior reaction.</p>"
