                            "title": "Hidden Illusions",
                            "description": "<p>Perhaps the most exciting secret is a compartment etched with<em> tromp l’oeil</em> (French for an optical illusion that “fools the eye”). The imagery includes Coaci’s calling card with a picture of the ruined Temple of Venus (actually a bath) in Baia, Italy; Salvator Rosa’s drawing of an old warrior; a <em>roscone</em> (a stylized rosette commonly found on antique temples); and a musical score that may have been composed by Coaci himself.</p>"
