            "id": "2251",
            "description": "<p>Thirty-six women have made a gift for someone special in their community: an album quilt. Each woman decorated and signed a single square of fabric, each with a distinct pattern—some geometric, some floral.</p><p>Album quilts like this became popular in Baltimore in the 1840s. They were inspired by the trend of signature albums, in which women collected their friends’ signatures, sayings, and drawings as a keepsake.</p>",
