                            "description": "<p>The horse is unrealistically diminutive, relative to the rider, but the native African horse—the Barb or Berber horse, known for its hardiness and fiery temperament—actually is pretty small. Of course, its size may simply reflect the fact that the sculpture was carved from a single tree trunk, and the horse could only be as long as the trunk was wide.</p>"
