                            "title": "Poetic Gathering",
                            "description": "<p>The famous convening of scholar-officials in 353 happened during the annual Spring Purification Festival, when cleansing rituals would be performed to prevent disease. Wang Xizhi gathered the group at the Orchid Pavilion in the eastern Chinese city of Shaoxing. They held a literary drinking contest: wine cups were floated down a small winding creek; whenever a cup stopped, the man closest to the cup was required to empty it and write a poem. </p>"
