                            "title": "The Calligraphy",
                            "description": "<p>By the end of the event, 26 participants had composed 37 poems. Wang Xizhi was asked to write a preface to the collection. Written in semi-cursive script, it ranks as one of the world’s best-known and most-copied works of literature.</p>"
