                            "description": "<p>The central amulet depicts the gods Shiva and Parvati seated on Shiva’s bull mount.  They sit beneath the gateway of a south Indian temple (<em>gopuram</em>), and are flanked by their two sons, the elephant-faced Ganesha and Murugan, who rides a peacock.  </p>",
