                            "attachments": [],
                            "description": "<p>Indian artisans traditionally adorn works of art, both big and small, with intricate and hidden details. Though this clasp would have been somewhat obscured by the wearer’s neck, it is adorned by the goddess Kaumari, the female counterpart of the god Murugan, who rides a peacock mount. She is flanked by two female attendants.</p>",
