                            "title": "A Dying Sage",
                            "description": "<p>Paintings of the Buddha's death are among the most important icons in the Buddhist faith. After the 1100s, the depictions were relatively consistent, with the Buddha lying on his right side, his head resting on his right arm on a large bed. This is how the scene is described in scripture, and image after image features the same symbols and similar placement of objects and beings. &nbsp;</p>"
