                            "title": "Setting the Scene",
                            "description": "<p>Buddhist scripture describes the day Sakyamuni died. He directed his cousin to prepare a bed in a grove of sāla trees near Kushinagar (present-day Uttar Pradesh, in India). The trees are considered sacred in Buddhism and the other Asian religious traditions that are rooted in India. In the painting, eight sāla (or sal) trees form the backdrop of Sakyamuni’s deathbed. </p>"
