                            "title": "Mythological Animals",
                            "description": "<p>In addition to real animals, the painting shows two fictional creatures: a white elephant and a blue lion. In Buddhist tradition, they are usually ridden by the Buddha's two attendants, Samantabhadra (Fugen) and Manjusri (Monju). Here, without their riders, they mourn with the other animals. </p>"
