                            "attachments": [],
                            "description": "<p>Most Japanese hanging scrolls have a decorative silk border. Less common is a hand-painted border like this one, which intersperses birds and flowers with so-called Dharma-chakra, or Wheels of the Buddhist Law, which symbolize the Buddha's teachings.&nbsp;</p>",
