                            "title": "Ox Skulls",
                            "description": "<p>Piranesi had a thing for ox skulls, particularly the decorative, twirling horns, and argued that the ancients did, too. In Classical art, the skulls were often paired with wreaths to represent sacrificial oxen. </p>"
