                            "title": "Unsuspected Color",
                            "description": "<p>In his memoirs, Wassily Kandinsky reflected on the surprising impact of color in Monet’s work. The Russian-born painter, a leader of the abstract art movement in the early 1900s, described his delight in the \"unsuspected power of the palette, previously concealed from me, which exceeded all my dreams.”</p>"
