                            "title": "South Wall – Pavilion and performance",
                            "description": "<p>Setting out snacks and drinks didn’t cut it at aristocratic Chinese parties—you needed dinner and a show. Families would have stages built in their private gardens. This one is rather simple and the atmosphere is decidedly casual, with the audience walking and talking during the performance.</p>"
