                            "title": "South Wall – Theater and Amusements",
                            "description": "<p>Women and men are segregated in this scene, watching the play from separate chambers. Women also didn’t gamble, but there were no such restrictions on buying a treat of sugar cane. Painted folding or flat fans provided artistic relief from warm weather.</p>"
