                            "title": "North Wall – Three Daoist immortals",
                            "description": "<p>The legendary Eight Immortals of Chinese lore each represent a different condition of youth: poverty, wealth, age, youth, etc. Here, to the left of the fireplace, the story of the immortals magically crossing the Eastern Sea is enacted in a parade, with three immortals standing on shells and a water-filled casket.</p>"
