                            "description": "<p>The plants thrive in summer with the help of constant irrigation. Water is supplied via the “dragon’s backbone machine,” a type of chain pump—sometimes called a “water ladder”—that was developed in China. Operated by foot, pallets draw water from below through a flume or trough.</p>",
