                            "title": "Fall",
                            "description": "<p>In the fall, the harvested rice is stacked and then threshed—by flailing, treading, or grinding in a mortar—to loosen the hulls. The rice grains are separated from their husks, called chaff, by tossing them above a sheet or mat.</p>"
