                            "title": "Politics and Art",
                            "description": "<p>Government censors initially approved publication of <em>Rue Transnonain</em>, but King Louis Philippe later ordered the confiscation and destruction of the lithographic printing stone and all unsold impressions of the print. Only a few original impressions survived. </p>"
