                            "title": "The Father",
                            "description": "<p>The central and largest figure in the scene is the dead father, bathed in bright moonlight. As the head of the household, he represents the family, their security, and well-being and recalls traditional depictions of the dead Christ, linking the innocence of Jesus with that of the family. </p>"
