                            "title": "Light Up My Life",
                            "description": "<p>Even among the fair’s stunning panoply of minarets and domes, the Electric Tower stood out: 410 feet tall and studded with 44,000 electric lights, it could be seen from Niagara Falls—the source of its power—some 20 miles away. At night, all of the exposition’s buildings were lit up, a never-before-seen sight. Most urban homes in the United States were not electrified until the 1930s and in rural areas the wait was even longer. </p>"
