                            "title": "Columbia",
                            "description": "<p>The damsel in classical Greek get-up, dreamily strumming a lyre, is Columbia, a personification of the United States. Her name derives from Christopher Columbus, then considered the “discoverer” of America. She appears here as an unnecessary reminder of who won the Civil War—and, more importantly, who lost. </p>"
