                            "title": "Dung Beetles",
                            "description": "<p>Yes, that’s a ball of poop. Dung beetles lay their eggs in the stuff, roll it into a sphere, then bury it. Usually associated with Africa—the famous Egyptian scarab is a type of dung beetle—they were also a relatively common sight in agricultural America where there was plenty of dung to go around. Why this one is labeled “UNION” is unclear.</p>"
