                            "description": "<p>These spangles, sparkling in the sunlight, are cut, shaped, and punched from thin aluminum sheets sold specifically for Egungun costumes. The dazzling effects date to the mid-20th-century aesthetic called “Shine-Shine.” Costumes like this, dating to the 1930s or1940s, are now considered old-fashioned. Newer Egungun costumes are sometimes created entirely from metallic fabrics, satins, sequins, and spangles.</p>\n",
