                            "description": "<p>The Red Cliff, now a favorite tourist spot, didn’t become famous for its tranquility. Situated along the middle section of China’s Yangzi River, it was the sight of a monumental battle around 208–209 that overturned Northern rule over Southern allied states.</p>",
