                            "description": "<p>Su Shi was one of the most influential scholar-officials of the Northern Song dynasty during his lifetime, famed for both his statesmanship and his art as a calligrapher, writer, and poet. After Su Shi died in 1107, his reputation continued to grow as shrines and memorials were erected in his honor and connoisseurs collected his poems and calligraphy. </p>",
