                            "description": "<p><em>After a while, the moon rose above the eastern mountain, and hovered between the Dipper and the Cowherd star. White mist lay across the water; the light from the water reached the sky.</em></p><p>That’s the translation of Su Shi’s verse—he would have called the big dipper “the northern ladle.” It’s one of the few constellations found in both Eastern and Western stargazing traditions. </p>",
