                            "attachments": [],
                            "description": "<p>On the morning of April 11, 1945, <em>LIFE </em>magazine photographer Margaret Bourke-White accompanied the legendary General George Patton and his Third Army troops into the concentration camp at Buchenwald. The was the first such camp seen by the Americans, and Bourke-White would provide the first images. </p>",
                            "title": "The First Camp"
