                            "title": "Where's Max?",
                            "description": "<p>Maximilian's rise to Holy Roman Emperor had to be confirmed by electors, and the Arch makes the case for him, arguing that his vast empire and political alliances qualify him to hold the throne. His wife, Mary of Burgundy, is seated to his right. Joanna of Castile, his daughter-in-law, is to his left—the faces of strategic marriages that added the Netherlands, Spain, and parts of France to the Habsburg Empire. </p>"
