                            "attachments": [],
                            "title": "Harpies",
                            "description": "<p>Harpies perch on either side of the main gate, symbolic monsters described by the ancient poet Virgil as having the faces of young women, unclean bodies, misshapen limbs, and a hungry, greedy expression. Their presence is a reminder of what Maximilian claimed <em>not </em>to be tempted by: lustful desire. </p>"
