                            "title": "Shields",
                            "description": "<p>Three small shields in the lower right symbolize the arch's major creative contributors: Court historian Johann Stabius, court architect Jorg Kolderer, and artist Albrecht Dürer. Although Dürer was more famous than the others, he was of lower social rank, so he made his shield the smallest. It shows opened double doors: \"Dürer\" is a variation of the German word \"Tür,\" meaning gate. </p>"
