                            "title": "Egyptian Hieroglyphs",
                            "description": "<p>Well-educate men like Maximilian knew of Egyptian hieroglyphs, and the creators of the Arch thought of the creatures surrounding Maximilian as a similar kind of writing with pictures. The lion refers to Maximilian's pwer, the eagle his wisdom. The feet standing on water suggests his ability to do the impossible. </p>"
