                            "description": "<p>The main setting of the last chapters of The Tale of Genji is the town of Uji near Kyoto   The consort Ukifune had committed suicide over the impossible position the advances of both Prince Niou, Genji’s nephew, and Kagero had put her in. The two men mourn her suicide and compose poems in her honor.</p>",
