                            "title": "Film as Art?",
                            "description": "<p>Kentridge was dedicated to drawing at first, needing to be convinced of film’s artistic potential. \"When I first did the films, they were very separate from my activity of drawing, which was art,” he says. “And when a curator came and said he wanted to show my films, I felt insulted and I refused. I said, 'This is nonsense; they're not art, they're films. Here are the drawings, what's wrong with the drawings? Why don't you like the drawings? These are perfectly good drawings, what do you want the films for?'\" </p>"
