            "id": "122115",
            "description": "<p>A single rock, a tangle of bamboo, and a distant mountain, all heavy with snow on a frigid winter’s evening. At right, a Chinese poem. The only materials: ink and a touch of gold paint on paper. Yet embedded within this seemingly simple composition is no less than a thousand years’ worth of Chinese and Japanese painting and poetry involving a Japanese painter, seven Zen priests, a courtier, and a smattering of poets and painters from Chinese antiquity.</p>",
