                            "title": "Pear skin",
                            "description": "<p>This set features a variety of lacquer techniques. Here, gold and silver foil are crushed and sprinkled onto the surface while the lacquer is still wet. It is called \"pear skin ground\" (<em>nashiji</em>) since it resembles the lightly speckled skin of an Asian pear. </p>"
