            "id": "122492",
            "description": "<p>Need to impress guests at your next cherry blossom viewing party? Try this luxurious picnic set, originally made for a well-heeled fashionista in Japan in the 1800s and adorned with gold, silver, and lacquer in an array of colors and designs. It has built-in food boxes to hold an assortment of goodies (everything from rice balls, pickled fruits, and veggies to delicate sweets) and the plates to serve them on. No one will go thirsty—the set includes a generously sized bottle for pouring sake. All of this fits into an elegant, lightweight frame with a handle, so it can be carried out onto the veranda or beneath a canopy of cherry blossoms in the garden. </p>",
