                            "title": "Spice Islands",
                            "description": "<p>This trio of figures hails from Banda and Maluku, also known as the \"Spice Islands,\" located between Indonesia and New Guinea. The Japanese were actually quite familiar with these southwest Pacific islands—throughout the early 1600s, Dutch traders employed Japanese mercenaries as they fought the rival British. They also exploited and massacred the native islanders. </p>"
